---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '~/components/PageHero.astro';
import Prose from '~/components/Prose.astro';
import { site } from '~/config/site';

const title = 'Privacy policy — RaySmartSolar';
const description =
  'Plain-language privacy policy: what our forms collect, where it goes, what stays on your device, and how to ask us to delete it. No legalese walls.';
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="The fine print"
    title="Privacy, in plain words."
    lede="What we collect, why, where it goes, and how to make us forget you — written to be read, not to protect us from you."
  />

  <section class="section pt-8">
    <div class="wrap">
      <Prose>
        <p class="mono-num" style="font-size: 0.78rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em;">
          Effective 6 July 2026
        </p>

        <div class="note">
          <strong>The short version:</strong> we collect what you type into our forms so we can
          reply to you. It goes to {site.email} and stays confidential. Nothing is sold. Your
          calculator fiddling stays on your own device. Email us to see or delete anything we hold.
        </div>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Forms</strong> (quote, contact, call-back, guide): your name, phone number, and
            whatever else the form asks — city, monthly bill figure, your message, sometimes an
            email address.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Calculator &amp; quote drafts:</strong> inputs like your bill amount are saved
            in your browser’s local storage so you don’t lose your place. They stay on your device
            and reach us only if you press submit.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics, if enabled:</strong> anonymous event counts (e.g. “calculator
            opened”) so we know which pages actually help. No advertising trackers, no cross-site
            profiles, no behavioural data brokers.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why we collect it</h2>
        <p>
          One reason: to answer you. A name and a number let us respond to your inquiry, arrange
          the survey you asked for, and prepare your quote. We don’t add you to broadcast marketing
          lists — if we ever want to send you anything beyond your own inquiry, we’ll ask first.
        </p>

        <h2>Where your information goes</h2>
        <p>
          Form submissions are delivered by email to
          <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> and read by the small number of people
          who need them to reply. Leads stay confidential: we don’t sell, rent, trade or “share
          with partners”. Ever.
        </p>

        <h2>A note on WhatsApp</h2>
        <p>
          If you talk to us on WhatsApp, that conversation lives on WhatsApp and is governed by
          WhatsApp’s (Meta’s) own terms and privacy policy, in addition to ours. Ask us anytime and
          we’ll delete our side of a chat.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies &amp; local storage</h2>
        <p>
          We set no cookies. Your browser’s local storage holds a few conveniences — your theme
          choice (day or dusk) and any unsent form or calculator drafts. All of it stays on your
          device, never reaches our servers by itself, and disappears if you clear your browsing
          data.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> — from the address you used, or
          mentioning the phone number you gave us — and we’ll tell you what we hold about you,
          correct it, or delete it. Deletion requests are honoured promptly and confirmed back to
          you.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          If this policy changes, the new version appears here with a new effective date. Anything
          unclear? <a href="/contact">Ask a human</a> — that offer covers the fine print too.
        </p>
      </Prose>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
